The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Feb. 18: Container Corporation of India and Ircon are planning to jointly bid for constructing and operating rail lines and container depots in Jordan, Nigeria, Mozambique and Saudi Arabia. Ircon is also planning to diversify into real estate and power projects, budget hotels and bid for Chandigarh?s monorail project. It is looking for suitable partners in each of these categories. 

 New Delhi, Feb. 18: The government today said it was against privatisation of public sector banks. Union minister of state for commerce Jairam Ramesh said privatisation of PSU banks was never on the government?s agenda, but consolidation and mergers were the need of the hour and the bank employees should improve their work culture.

 Ludhiana, Feb. 18: Avon group founder Hansraj Pahwa today died due to illness. He was 95 and is survived by a younger brother and daughter in law. His only son Inderjit Singh Pahwa died a month ago.




